  "tips": [
    {
      "tipDesc": "You can add 1 tbsp cream instead of milk to add texture and sweetness."
    },
    {
      "tipDesc": "Making fresh paneer is easy. Boil 3 cups of milk and then add 2 tbsp lemon juice. Milk will start to curdle, else add some more lemon juice. Keep stirring the milk during this step so the milk does not stick to bottom. Once entire milk has curdled, immediately drain the milk in muslin or cheese cloth. The drained portion collected is Paneer. Wait till the water is drained completely. Take a plate and put the muslin cloth with curdled milk. On top of it, place a heavy plate. and let it sit for 45 mins. Remove the Paneer from cloth and it is ready to use in your dish."
    }
